<TITLE> Tigers learning something new everyday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 13 (bdnews24.com) - The Tigers are learning something with the passing of new each day in their six-day training under the Bangladesh Army. The third day, Monday saw three new schedules of activities. Following experiences in climbing buildings and mountains, rappelling and snorkelling in the first two days in Sylhet, the cricketers Monday went through hiking, hallow casting and confidence walk and sliding in Sylhet along with the regular schedule of self-criticism and counselling. "We are returning from Tamabil where the boys had to hike between high and low hills and bushes and they had to cross an area about 16km," national team manager Tanjib Ahsan Saad told bdnews24.com by telephone Monday. The three and a half hours session of hiking ended at 6:30pm before the two and a half hours session of hallow casting, confidence walk and sliding had started at 11:00am. Except Alok Kapali, with a left toe injury, all members of 13-member squad took part in the third day's training Monday. "We have just got the Alok's X-ray report and the physio is to scan it tonight. You will know about it Tuesday," said Saad. "There is nothing to be worried according to the physio and we hope Alok will be fit soon," said the former national cricketer. bdn
